.:: Puzzle 3x4-Level-2-20::.
There 4 different types of food: tomato, kale, cranberry, nectarine
4 different pets are kept: lizard, frog, chinchilla, rat
The people use 4 different means of transport: car, bike, subway, train
1. the owner of the lizard is on the far left##1
2. the person eating tomato is on the right of the owner of the frog##1
3. the person driving the bike is on the right of the owner of the lizard##1
4. the person eating cranberry is on the far right##1
5. the person driving the train is the owner of the rat##1
6. the owner of the frog is between the person eating nectarine and the person driving the subway##2

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1      |    2    |     3     |     4      |
| Food        | nectarine | kale | tomato | cranberry |
| Pet         | lizard       | frog     | chinchilla   | rat   |
| Transport   | car | bike | subway | train |

 